-- Adelaide Bank shareholders ok takeover by Bendigo
-- 
-- Sun Nov 11, 2007 11:17pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/12/us-adelaidebank-bendigo-idUSSYU00347820071112

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Adelaide Bank Ltd ADB.AX shareholders approved a A$1.57 billion ($1.43 billion) takeover by regional lender Bendigo Bank Ltd ( BEN.AX ), an Adelaide Bank official told Reuters on Monday. 

 About 98 percent of shareholders voted in favor of the deal, the official said. The takeover will create Australia's seventh-biggest lender by market value, with total assets worth about A$50 billion. Trading in the shares of both companies was halted ahead of the vote. ($1=A$1.10) (Reporting by  Denny Thomas ;)